 410 @tf_export('stats_accumulator_scalar_flush')
 411 def stats_accumulator_scalar_flush(stats_accumulator_handle, stamp_token, next_stamp_token, name=None):
 412   r"""Flushes the scalar stats accumulator to output and resets the internal state.
 413 
 414   Args:
 415     stats_accumulator_handle: A `Tensor` of type `resource`.
 416       handle to the stats accumulator.
 417     stamp_token: A `Tensor` of type `int64`.
 418       Stamp token for Read/Write operations.
 419       Any operation with a mismatching token will be dropped.
 420     next_stamp_token: A `Tensor` of type `int64`.
 421       Stamp token for the next iteration.
 422     name: A name for the operation (optional).
 423 
 424   Returns:
 425     A tuple of `Tensor` objects (num_updates, output_partition_ids, output_feature_ids, output_gradients, output_hessians).
 426 
 427     num_updates: A `Tensor` of type `int64`. Number of times stats were added to this accumulator since last
 428           flush.
 429       output_partition_ids A vector of partition_ids for the slots.
 430     output_partition_ids: A `Tensor` of type `int32`.
 431     output_feature_ids: A `Tensor` of type `int64`. Rank 2 tensor of feature id and feature dimension ids.
 432     output_gradients: A `Tensor` of type `float32`. A vector of gradients, with a value for each slot
 433       in <output_partition_id, output_feature_id>.
 434     output_hessians: A `Tensor` of type `float32`. A vector of hessians, with a value for each slot
 435       in <output_partition_id, output_feature_id>.
 436   """
 437   _ctx = _context._context
 438   if _ctx is None or not _ctx._eager_context.is_eager:
 439     _, _, _op = _op_def_lib._apply_op_helper(
 440         "StatsAccumulatorScalarFlush",
 441         stats_accumulator_handle=stats_accumulator_handle,
 442         stamp_token=stamp_token, next_stamp_token=next_stamp_token, name=name)
 443     _result = _op.outputs[:]
 444     _inputs_flat = _op.inputs
 445     _attrs = None
 446     _execute.record_gradient(
 447       "StatsAccumulatorScalarFlush", _inputs_flat, _attrs, _result, name)
 448     _result = _StatsAccumulatorScalarFlushOutput._make(_result)
 449     return _result
 450
